{
  "root": {
    "children": [
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "How do you translate a series that's entire gimmick was based on the Wii's motion controls? It's a tough question, but they figured it out with the Switch, making it a handheld must - lite users, this one's perfect for you. Graphics inspired by the pre-NES era, a treat and a rarity in the indie space (with most opting for that 8bit nostalgic overdose), a variety of different homages whether to pong, runners or shoot-em-ups, and a finale that ties all these classic genres into one? ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Bit.Trip ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "takes simplicity and does wonders with it. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "embed",
        "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mEq5dJw80iY",
